hey will be removed from the guild. (In the unlikely event of this happening the sponsor will lose sponsorship privileges for a minimum of 30 days.)<br><br>5        Once a Keeper has been with the guild for 30 days they may be promoted to a higher rank by their class leader (for Knights) or any officer capable (for Artisans). At this time they may sponsor other Squires of their own. This promotion is at the discretion of the promoting officer.<br><br>6        Promotion to levels higher than Knight must be approved by a 2/3 majority vote of all officers or by the Guildleader or Executive Officer(s) at their discretion.<br><br>7        Known individuals, from real life, other games, etc. may be invited into the guild immediately at an appropriate rank.<br><br><br>Note:  These are listed as guidelines.  They are not hard and fast rules.  Exceptional circumstances can, and will, arise where a member may be promoted to a higher level without going through the normal procedures.  These will definitely be the exception, not the rule.  If an individual has a problem with a promotion, or lack thereof, they may appeal it to an officer for investigation and resolution.<br><br> <p>--<br><center><img src="http://home.twcny.rr.com/blackros/sig1.gif" border="0"></center></p><i></i></td></tr></table> </td></tr></table> <table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top"> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub31.ezboard.com/fforgottengrailkeepersfrm8.showPrevMessage?topicID=60.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub31.ezboard.com/fforgottengrailkeepersfrm8.showNextMessage?topicID=60.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br></td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"> <a href=http://pub31.ezboard.com/fforgottengrailkeepersfrm8.emailToFriend?topicID=60.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/image/email.gif border=0 alt="Email This To a Friend"> Email This To a Friend</a><br> <a href=http://pub31.ezboard.